This topic describes how <%= vars.product_full %> (<%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>) administrators
can create and delete network profiles for Kubernetes clusters provisioned by <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> on vSphere with NSX-T.
It also lists verified use cases for network profiles on <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %>.

For more information on how to use network profiles, see [Using Network Profiles (NSX-T Only)](./network-profiles.html).

## <a id="create"></a> Create a Network Profile

To create a network profile in <%= vars.product_short %>:

1. Define a network profile configuration in a JSON file. 
For more information, see [Network Profile Format](#format) below.

1. Apply the network profile to <%= vars.product_short %> using the <%= vars.k8s_runtime_abbr %> CLI.
For more information, see [The create-network-profile Command](#run-create) below.

### <a id="format"></a> Network Profile Format

